The National Testing Agency (NTA) has released UGC NET Admit Card for June 2023 Cycle. The exam is scheduled from 13th June to 22nd June 2023. Aspiring candidates across the nation can now download their UGC NET 2023 Admit Card from the official website ugcnet.nta.nic.in. The release of the admit card marks a crucial step for candidates who are preparing to appear for the prestigious UGC NET examination. With the NTA taking charge of the examination process, the issuance of the admit card ensures a smooth and organized conduct of the UGC NET 2023. Aspirants are urged to promptly download their NTA UGC NET Admit Card to avoid any last-minute hassles and to stay updated with the latest examination details.
Candidates who have successfully applied for the exam will be able to download their admit card by entering their application number and date of birth on the NTA's official website. The UGC NET admit card will include important details such as the candidate's name, roll number, exam date and time, exam centre address, and instructions. However, the NTA has not yet released the application process for the June cycle of UGC NET 2023.

  • The UGC NET exam date, timing, and location of the exam centre will be specified on the admit card.

Steps to Download UGC NET 2023 Admit Card 

Candidates are required to download their hall tickets through NTA’s official website as no hard copies of the same will be sent to them. The steps to download the UGC NET Hall Ticket 2023 have been explained below.

Direct Link to Download UGC NET Phase I Admit Card

Step 1: Click the direct link above to download the NTA UGC NET Admit Card.

Step 2: Candidates are required to enter their Login ID, date of birth, and security pin correctly.

Step 3: Click on the login button provided.

Step 4: Your UGC NET Admit Card will appear on your screen.

Step 5: Alternatively, you can also visit the UGC NET Official Website.

Step 6: The homepage of UGC NET will appear.

Step 7: Click the link “Download UGC NET Admit Card 2023”

Step 8: Repeat the steps above mentioned downloading the admit card.

Step 9: Download it and take a print out of your NTA UGC NET admit card.

Step 10: Keep it safe for future reference.

Steps to Download UGC NET City Intimation Letter

The UGC NET City Intimation Letter has been released for the Phase III examination which is scheduled from 3rd to 6th March 2023. Below is the direct link to download the letter.

Direct Link to Download UGC NET City Intimation Letter

Step 1: Click on the direct link mentioned above.

Step 2: Enter the login credentials Application Number, Date of Birth and Security Pin.

Step 3: Click on Submit Button.

Step 4: Download and take a printout of the City Intimation Letter.

Direct Link to Download NTA UGC NET Admit Card or Hall Ticket

The direct link to download the NTA UGC NET admit card or hall ticket will be available on the official website of the National Testing Agency (NTA). To access the admit card, you need to visit the official NTA website, and then click on the link for the UGC NET admit card. You will be required to enter your login credentials, such as your application number and date of birth, to access the admit card. It is important to note that the admit card is a crucial document and must be carried to the exam center on the day of the exam. Failure to do so will result in the candidate not being allowed to appear for the test. It is advisable to download and print a few copies of the admit card for future reference. Direct link to download the NTA UGC NET admit card will also be added shortly after it gets released by the official website. 

Direct link to download the NTA UGC NET admit card

Things to Remember while Downloading UGC NET Admit Card Card 2023

Keep in mind the following details while downloading your NTA UGC NET Admit Card for the exam:

  • Smooth Internet Connection
  • Keep your Login details ready which includes Login ID, Password
  • We advise candidates to enter captcha very carefully.
  • Delay in access to the page may occur, don't get panicked in this situation, you can wait for some time and try again. 
  • Download the Admit Card on your computer.
  •  Make sure your Printer is in working condition.
  • Double-check the Printed details carefully.

UGC NET Exam City Intimation 2023

NTA releases exam city intimation before releasing the admit card to give candidates prior information regarding their UGC NET exam center’s city so that they can make travel arrangements in advance. Candidates will be able to know the UGC NET exam city 2023 allotted to them by following the given steps:

  1. Visit the official website
  2. Click on the ‘Advance Exam City Intimation’ link.
  3. Login using the application number, date of birth, and security pin.
  4. Check your exam city.
  5. Take a printout for future use.

Details Mentioned on UGC NET Admit Card 2023

As soon as candidates download their UGC NET 2023 Admit Card they are advised to check all the printed details mentioned on it carefully. Candidates must note that the details mentioned on the admit card must match with the UGC NET application details filled at the time of registration.

  • Date of birth
  • Application number
  • Category (General, SC, ST,OBC)
  • Test city 
  • Exam Center address
  • Subject
  • Photograph & signature 
  • Candidate’s name

Errors to Check in the UGC NET Admit Card 2023

The information mentioned on your UGC NTA NET Hall ticket 2023 must be correct in all senses. To ensure the same, candidates must check the following details mentioned on the admit card carefully

  • Spelling of their name
  • Date of birth
  • Subject code opted for
  • Spelling of parent/guardian’s name
  • Application/Registration number
  • Exam date and time

How To Correct Information on UGC NET Admit Card 2023?

  • In case, a candidate is unable to download his/her admit card or there is any discrepancy in the printed particulars given on the admit card then he/she should call at the helpline numbers of NTA - 8076535482 and 7703859909. Candidates must call on these numbers on working days from 10:00 AM to 5:30 PM. 
  • In case of any error on the NTA UGC NET admit card, the official website of the exam states, “In such cases, candidates can appear in the examination with the already downloaded Admit Card. However, the officials will take the required action to make corrections in the record later.” 

Know the Eligibility criteria for UGC NET exam here!

Problems while Downloading UGC NET Admit Card Download 2023

Even though the process to download the UGC NET hall ticket is simple, candidates may at times face issues in downloading the same. Some of the reasons for this include the following;

  • Incomplete application form: Candidates will not be issued the admit card if their application form is found to be incomplete or incorrectly filled.
  • Non-fulfillment of eligibility criteria: Applicants who are found to be ineligible by the authorities will not be allowed to appear for the exam. Hence, they will not be issued admit cards. Reasons for being ineligible could be uploading incomplete/incorrect documents or non-fulfillment of age and qualification requirements.
  • Incorrect login details: It is likely that the candidate may not be able download her/his NTA UGC NET admit card because of entering the wrong credentials while logging in.
  • Interrupted internet supply: Candidates may not be able to download their hall tickets due to interrupted or slow internet connection. At times, heavy traffic on the site may also slow down or hamper the download process.

Documents You Must Carry to the Exam Hall with Admit Card

Candidates are advised to carry some important documents in the examination hall along with your UGC NET 2023. You must carry a valid Photo Identity (along with a photocopy) which could be any one of the following as mentioned below.

1) UGC NET Admit Card 2023

2) Passport Size Photo

3) Photo IDs Proof

  • Driving Licence
  • Voter ID
  • Passport
  • Aadhaar Card (with photo)
  • Ration Card/PAN Card

Make sure that the identity cards you carry are original, valid, and non-expired.

4) PwD certificate, if applicable.

Things not to carry at the exam center

The following things must be avoided during UGC NET 2023.

  • Electronic Devices like Mobile phones, Electronic Watches is strictly prohibited for examination
  • Calculators are not allowed in UGC NET Exam
  • Avoid wearing heavy Jewelry 
  • Any printed paper which may look suspicious.

Carrying the above-mentioned things will lead to direct termination of candidates from the exam. Therefore we advise you to read the complete list before you go for UGC NET 2023.

What Next after the UGC NET Admit Card?

Once the NTA UGC Admit Card has been released, the candidates must download and print the same. Also, as the exam will be scheduled in the next few days of the admit card release, you must set your focus on revision of important topics, practising important questions, and solving UGC previous year’s papers and mock tests to help with the last minute preparation. After the UGC NET admit card release, the following steps typically occur:

  • Candidates download their UGC NET admit card: They should check the details printed on the admit card and ensure they are correct.
  • Preparation for the exam: Candidates should review the syllabus and study materials, and make sure they are fully prepared for the UGC exam.
  • Reporting to the exam center: On the day of the exam, candidates should report to the exam center with their admit card and any other required documents.
  • Verification of identity: Candidates will typically undergo identity verification processes such as biometric authentication or signature verification by the NTA.
  • Writing the exam: Candidates will follow the instructions given by the invigilator and write the UGC exam as per the given guidelines.
  • Result declaration: After the exam is over, the examination authority will announce the results on their official website or through other designated platforms.

UGC NET Selection Process

The UGC NET exam is a qualifying examination which determines the eligibility of candidates for the posts of Assistant Professor and Junior Research Fellow in various Government Universities across the country. Candidates who qualify the exam can apply for these posts. The selection criteria for appointment to these posts will depend on the university/institute to which one applies.

Latest UGC NET Updates

Last updated: Jun 8, 2023

UGC NET Admit Card has been released by the National Testing Agency. The Phase – I Examination is scheduled to take place from 13th June to 17th June 2023. The Phase II Exam will be conducted from 19th to 22nd June 2023. The UGC-NET June 2023 exam will take place in CBT mode for more than 80 subjects, with the purpose of determining eligibility for ‘Junior Research Fellowship’ and ‘Assistant Professor’. The UGC NET CBT exam pattern consists of two papers - Paper I and Paper II. Paper I consists of 50 questions and Paper II consists of 100 questions. The candidates who are preparing for the exam can check the UGC NET Previous Year Papers which helps you to check the difficulty level of the exam. Applicants can also attempt the UGC NET Test Series which helps you to find your strengths and weakness.

UGC NET Admit Card 2023 FAQs

What is the last date to download the admit card?
The last date to download the admit card will be the day of the exam.
What if I forgot to carry the Admit card at the exam center?
You will not be allowed to enter the examination hall without an admit card.
Is there any interview in UGC NET Exam 2023?
No there is no interview test for UGC NET Exam 2023.
How can I download my UGC NET admit card in case I forget my UGC NET login password?
If you forget your login password, you can create a new password by clicking the Forgot User ID/Password button on the Registered Candidate login window. The link to reset your password will be sent to your registered email address.
How can I download net 2023 admit card?
Candidates can download their UGC NET admit card from the official website of NTA.
Is UGC NET admit card available?
Yes, the admit card is available on the official website.
On which website UGC Net admit card 2023 will be released?
On the official website, UGC Website , UGC admit card 2023 is released.
Is UGC NET Admit Card for Phase 1 available?
Yes, the UGC NET Admit Card for Phase 1 is available for download at ugcnet.nta.nic.in, the UGC's official website.
